doc.previous: Boeing delivered Qatar's first C-17 on 11 August 2009 and the second on 10 September 2009 for the Qatar Emiri Air Force.[151] Qatar received its third C-17 in 2012, and fourth C-17 was received on 10 December 2012.[152] In June 2013, the New York Times reported that Qatar was allegedly using its C-17s to ship weapons from Libya to the Syrian opposition during the civil war via Turkey.[153]
doc.after: In February 2009, the United Arab Emirates Air Force agreed to purchase four C-17s.[154] In January 2010, a contract was signed for six C-17s.[155] In May 2011, the first C-17 was handed over and the last of the six was received in June 2012.[156][157]
